{"abstract":[{"text":"Set up Ensembles to sync a Core Data persistent store across devices.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensembles synchronizes a Core Data SQLite store by recording local changes as events and exchanging them through a cloud backend. This guide walks through everything you need, starting with a complete working example using "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleContainer","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For SwiftData, see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SwiftDataIntegration","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Add Ensembles to Your Project","type":"heading","anchor":"Add-Ensembles-to-Your-Project","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add the Ensembles package to your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Package.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" or via Xcode’s package dependencies:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["https:\/\/github.com\/mentalfaculty\/Ensembles-3.git"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Import the core module and one cloud backend:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import Ensembles","import EnsemblesCloudKit   \/\/ or EnsemblesLocalFile, EnsemblesMemory"]},{"text":"Complete Example: Core Data with CloudKit","type":"heading","anchor":"Complete-Example-Core-Data-with-CloudKit","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here’s a complete, working setup for a SwiftUI app that syncs via CloudKit. This uses "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleContainer","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", which creates the Core Data stack for you and syncs automatically."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"1. Create Your Core Data Model","type":"heading","anchor":"1-Create-Your-Core-Data-Model","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Xcode, add a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".xcdatamodeld"},{"type":"text","text":" file to your project (e.g., "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Model.xcdatamodeld"}]},{"type":"text","text":"). Define your entities as usual. For this example, we’ll assume a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Note"},{"type":"text","text":" entity with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"title"},{"type":"text","text":" (String) and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"uniqueID"},{"type":"text","text":" (String) attributes."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"2-Define-Your-Model-with-Syncable","level":3,"text":"2. Define Your Model with `Syncable`"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For deduplication, conform your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSManagedObject"},{"text":" subclass to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/Syncable","type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol and specify which property holds the global identifier. A UUID assigned at creation time is usually the best choice:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import CoreData","import Ensembles","","class Note: NSManagedObject, Syncable {","    static let globalIdentifierKey = \"uniqueID\"","    @NSManaged var uniqueID: String","    @NSManaged var title: String","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A global identifier "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"must never change"}]},{"type":"text","text":" once it has been assigned. Changing it after sync has begun will cause duplicates or data loss."}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use a fixed, meaningful value instead of a UUID for singleton objects or reference data like tags, where two devices might independently create the same logical object."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"3. Set Up the Container","type":"heading","anchor":"3-Set-Up-the-Container","level":3},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import SwiftUI","import Ensembles","import EnsemblesCloudKit","","@main","struct MyApp: App {","    let syncContainer: CoreDataEnsembleContainer","","    init() {","        \/\/ The model URL points to the .momd bundle compiled from your .xcdatamodeld","        let modelURL = Bundle.main.url(forResource: \"Model\", withExtension: \"momd\")!","","        \/\/ This creates a full Core Data stack automatically:","        \/\/ - SQLite store at Application Support\/MyNotes.sqlite","        \/\/ - Main-queue viewContext for your UI","        \/\/ - Auto-sync on save, on app activation, and on a 5-minute timer","        let container = CoreDataEnsembleContainer(","            name: \"MyNotes\",","            modelURL: modelURL,","            cloudFileSystem: CloudKitFileSystem(","                ubiquityContainerIdentifier: \"iCloud.com.example.mynotes\"","            )","        )!","","        self.syncContainer = container","    }","","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            ContentView()","                .environment(","                    \\.managedObjectContext,","                    syncContainer.viewContext","                )","        }","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That’s the complete setup. The container discovers "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/Syncable"},{"type":"text","text":" conformances automatically, attaches to the cloud, and begins syncing. Remote changes are merged into "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"viewContext"},{"type":"text","text":" so your UI stays up to date."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"4. Respond to Events (Optional)","type":"heading","anchor":"4-Respond-to-Events-Optional","level":3},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Called after remote changes are merged into viewContext","container.didSaveMergeChanges = { notification in","    print(\"Merged remote changes\")","}","","\/\/ Called if a sync fails","container.didEncounterError = { error in","    print(\"Sync error: \\(error)\")","}"]},{"text":"Using a Custom Store Location","type":"heading","anchor":"Using-a-Custom-Store-Location","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need control over where the SQLite file lives, pass an explicit "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"storeURL"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let appSupport = FileManager.default.urls(","    for: .applicationSupportDirectory, in: .userDomainMask",").first!","let storeURL = appSupport.appendingPathComponent(\"MyApp\/data.sqlite\")","try FileManager.default.createDirectory(","    at: storeURL.deletingLastPathComponent(),","    withIntermediateDirectories: true",")","","let container = CoreDataEnsembleContainer(","    name: \"MyNotes\",","    storeURL: storeURL,","    modelURL: Bundle.main.url(forResource: \"Model\", withExtension: \"momd\")!,","    cloudFileSystem: CloudKitFileSystem(","        ubiquityContainerIdentifier: \"iCloud.com.example.mynotes\"","    )",")!"]},{"text":"Working with an Existing Core Data Stack","type":"heading","anchor":"Working-with-an-Existing-Core-Data-Stack","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you already have an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSPersistentContainer"},{"type":"text","text":", pass it in directly:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let container = CoreDataEnsembleContainer(","    persistentContainer: myPersistentContainer,","    cloudFileSystem: cloudFS",")"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Or if you have an existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSManagedObjectContext"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let container = CoreDataEnsembleContainer(","    name: \"MyNotes\",","    viewContext: myContext,","    persistentStoreURL: myStoreURL,","    managedObjectModel: myContext.persistentStoreCoordinator!.managedObjectModel,","    managedObjectModels: nil,","    cloudFileSystem: cloudFS",")"]},{"text":"Auto-Sync Configuration","type":"heading","anchor":"Auto-Sync-Configuration","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Control when syncing occurs with "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/AutoSyncPolicy","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let config = EnsembleContainerConfiguration(","    autoSyncPolicy: [.onSave, .onTimer],   \/\/ Sync on save and timer, not on activation","    timerInterval: 30                       \/\/ Timer fires every 30 seconds",")","let container = CoreDataEnsembleContainer(","    name: \"MyNotes\",","    modelURL: modelURL,","    cloudFileSystem: cloudFS,","    configuration: config",")"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"autoSyncPolicy"},{"type":"text","text":" to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".manual"},{"type":"text","text":" and call "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleContainer\/sync()"},{"type":"text","text":" yourself for full control over timing."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Backward Compatibility with Ensembles 2","type":"heading","anchor":"Backward-Compatibility-with-Ensembles-2","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you’re transitioning from Ensembles 2 and some users may still be on E2, set the compatibility mode:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let config = EnsembleContainerConfiguration(","    compatibilityMode: .ensembles2Compatible",")"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This restricts exports to formats that Ensembles 2 peers can parse. Switch to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".ensembles3"},{"type":"text","text":" (the default) once all users have upgraded."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"The Manual Way: CoreDataEnsemble","type":"heading","anchor":"The-Manual-Way-CoreDataEnsemble","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For more control over the sync lifecycle, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble"},{"type":"text","text":" directly. This is useful when you need to manage attach\/detach timing, handle specific delegate methods, or integrate with a complex Core Data stack."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Create and Attach","type":"heading","anchor":"Create-and-Attach","level":3},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import Ensembles","import EnsemblesCloudKit","","\/\/ Get the store URL from your persistent store coordinator","let store = persistentStoreCoordinator.persistentStores.first!","let storeURL = store.url!","let modelURL = Bundle.main.url(forResource: \"Model\", withExtension: \"momd\")!","","let ensemble = CoreDataEnsemble(","    ensembleIdentifier: \"MyNotes\",","    persistentStoreURL: storeURL,","    managedObjectModelURL: modelURL,","    cloudFileSystem: CloudKitFileSystem(","        ubiquityContainerIdentifier: \"iCloud.com.example.mynotes\"","    )",")","ensemble?.delegate = self","","\/\/ Attach registers this device in the cloud","try await ensemble?.attachPersistentStore()"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble\/ensembleIdentifier"},{"type":"text","text":" must be the same on all devices that should sync together. If you have multiple persistent stores, create one ensemble per store with a unique identifier."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Avoid saving to the persistent store while attaching. If a save is detected, attachment will fail with an error and you will need to retry."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"text":"Sync Changes","type":"heading","anchor":"Sync-Changes","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Call "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble\/sync(options:)"},{"type":"text","text":" periodically — for example, when the app enters the foreground, on a timer, or in response to a push notification:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["try await ensemble?.sync()"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A sync downloads remote events, replays them into the local store, and uploads new local events. Sync errors are usually transient — just retry later."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Handle the Delegate","type":"heading","anchor":"Handle-the-Delegate","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implement "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleDelegate"},{"type":"text","text":" to respond to sync events. The most important method merges remote changes into your main context:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["extension AppDelegate: CoreDataEnsembleDelegate {","    func coreDataEnsemble(","        _ ensemble: CoreDataEnsemble,","        didSaveMergeChangesWith notification: Notification","    ) {","        viewContext.perform {","            self.viewContext.mergeChanges(fromContextDidSave: notification)","        }","    }","}"]},{"name":"Tip","type":"aside","style":"tip","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSManagedObject"},{"type":"text","text":" subclasses conform to "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/Syncable"},{"type":"text","text":", you don’t need to implement "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"globalIdentifiersForManagedObjects"},{"type":"text","text":" — the ensemble discovers identifier properties automatically. You only need the delegate method if you use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CoreDataEnsemble"},{"type":"text","text":" directly without "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleContainer"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Other delegate methods let you:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inspect and repair merge data"}]},{"type":"text","text":" before it’s committed ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"shouldSaveMergedChangesIn:reparationContext:"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Handle save failures"}]},{"type":"text","text":" during merging ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"didFailToSaveMergedChangesIn:error:reparationContext:"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"React to forced detaches"}]},{"type":"text","text":" caused by identity changes or data corruption ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"didDetachWithError:"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/ConflictResolution"},{"type":"text","text":" for more on conflict handling and the reparation context."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Detach","type":"heading","anchor":"Detach","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To stop syncing, detach from the cloud:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["try await ensemble?.detachPersistentStore()"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This removes local sync data (event logs and metadata). The persistent store itself is not affected. You can re-attach later to resume syncing."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Seed Policies","type":"heading","anchor":"Seed-Policies","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SeedPolicy"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter controls how existing data in the store is handled during attachment:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SeedPolicy\/mergeAllData"},{"type":"text","text":" (default) — Imports local data so it can be merged with data from other devices."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SeedPolicy\/excludeLocalData"},{"type":"text","text":" — Ignores local data. Use this when you want to start fresh from cloud data."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Sync Options","type":"heading","anchor":"Sync-Options","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For advanced control, pass "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SyncOptions"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Download only — don't integrate or upload","try await ensemble?.sync(options: .cloudFileRetrievalOnly)","","\/\/ Force a rebase to compact sync history","try await ensemble?.sync(options: .forceRebase)"]},{"text":"Process Pending Changes","type":"heading","anchor":"Process-Pending-Changes","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On iOS, the app may be suspended before Ensembles finishes recording a save. Call "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble\/processPendingChanges()"},{"type":"text","text":" — for example, in a background task — to ensure all changes are fully stored:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["try await ensemble?.processPendingChanges()"]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Monitor Activity","anchor":"Monitor-Activity"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Track long-running operations via "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble\/currentActivity"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble\/activityProgress"},{"type":"text","text":", or observe these notifications:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"coreDataEnsembleDidBeginActivity"},{"type":"text","text":" — An activity started"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"coreDataEnsembleDidMakeProgressWithActivity","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — Progress updated (includes ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SyncingPhase","type":"reference"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/AttachingPhase","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":")","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"coreDataEnsembleWillEndActivity"},{"type":"text","text":" — An activity finished (may include an error)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/GettingStarted","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleContainer","doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble","doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleDelegate"],"title":"Essentials","generated":true,"anchor":"Essentials"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/ensembles\/gettingstarted"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Ensembles"}],"role":"article","title":"Getting Started"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"references":{"doc://Ensembles/documentation/Ensembles/AutoSyncPolicy":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AutoSyncPolicy","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ensembles\/autosyncpolicy","title":"AutoSyncPolicy","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AutoSyncPolicy","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/AutoSyncPolicy","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Controls when automatic merges occur.","type":"text"}]},"doc://Ensembles/documentation/Ensembles/CoreDataEnsemble/sync(options:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Syncs changes with other peers."}],"url":"\/documentation\/ensembles\/coredataensemble\/sync(options:)","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble\/sync(options:)","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"sync"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"options"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:9Ensembles11SyncOptionsV","text":"SyncOptions"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"async"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"}],"title":"sync(options:)"},"doc://Ensembles/documentation/Ensembles/CoreDataEnsembleContainer":{"title":"CoreDataEnsembleContainer","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/ensembles\/coredataensemblecontainer","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A high-level container that sets up a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble"},{"text":" with automatic syncing,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"delegate management, and optional Core Data stack creation.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleContainer","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CoreDataEnsembleContainer","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CoreDataEnsembleContainer"}]},"doc://Ensembles/documentation/Ensembles/CoreDataEnsemble/activityProgress":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The progress of the current activity, as a fraction between 0.0 and 1.0."}],"url":"\/documentation\/ensembles\/coredataensemble\/activityprogress","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble\/activityProgress","type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"activityProgress"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sf","text":"Float"}],"title":"activityProgress"},"doc://Ensembles/documentation/Ensembles/CoreDataEnsemble/ensembleIdentifier":{"fragments":[{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ensembleIdentifier","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"}],"title":"ensembleIdentifier","url":"\/documentation\/ensembles\/coredataensemble\/ensembleidentifier","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble\/ensembleIdentifier","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"A global identifier for the ensemble, used to match corresponding ensembles across devices.","type":"text"}]},"doc://Ensembles/documentation/Ensembles/CoreDataEnsembleContainer/sync()":{"title":"sync()","role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleContainer\/sync()","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Attach if needed and merge changes with peers."}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"sync","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() ","kind":"text"},{"text":"async","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/ensembles\/coredataensemblecontainer\/sync()"},"doc://Ensembles/documentation/Ensembles/SeedPolicy":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SeedPolicy"}],"title":"SeedPolicy","url":"\/documentation\/ensembles\/seedpolicy","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SeedPolicy"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SeedPolicy","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Controls how existing data in the persistent store is treated when attaching."}]},"doc://Ensembles/documentation/Ensembles/Syncable":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Syncable"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ensembles\/syncable","title":"Syncable","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Syncable"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/Syncable","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A protocol for model types that declare how to derive a global identifier"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for Ensembles deduplication."}]},"doc://Ensembles/documentation/Ensembles":{"titl